\section*{Christmas Morning Prayer: Benedictus}

\bigskip\lilypondfile[line-width=4.5\in]{Christmas-Lauds-Ben-Ant-Cantor.ly}

\indentpattern{01 1 0101 1001 101 101 101 101}
\begin{verse}
\begin{patverse}  

Blessed be the Lord, the G\pointup{o}d of Israel; *\\
he has come to his people and set th\pointup{e}m free.

He has raised up for us a m\pointup{\i}ghty savior, *\\
born of the house of his serv\pointup{a}nt, David.

Through his holy prophets he promised of \pointup{o}ld \dag\\
that he would save us fr\pointup{o}m our enemies, *\\
from the hands of all wh\pointup{o} hate us.\\
He promised to show mercy t\pointup{o} our fathers *\\
and to remember his hol\pointup{y} covenant.

This was the oath he swore to our f\pointup{a}ther, Abraham: *\\
to set us free from the hands of \pointup{o}ur enemies,\\
free to worship him without f\pointup{e}ar, \dag\\
holy and righteous \pointup{\i}n his sight *\\
all the days of \pointup{o}ur life.

\rightskip=-1cm You, my child, shall be called the prophet of th\pointup{e} Most High: *\\
\rightskip=0cm for you will go before the Lord to prepare h\pointup{\i}s way,\\
to give his people knowledge \pointup{o}f salvation *\\
by the forgiveness of th\pointup{e}ir sins.

In the tender compassion \pointup{o}f our God *\\
the dawn from on high shall break \pointup{u}pon us,\\
to shine on those who dwell in darkness and the shad\pointup{o}w of death, *\\
and to guide our feet into the way \pointup{o}f peace.

Glory to the Father, and t\pointup{o} the Son, *\\
and to the Hol\pointup{y} Spirit:\\
as it was in the beginn\pointup{\i}ng, is now, *\\
and will be forever, \pointup{A}men.

\end{patverse}
\end{verse}

